{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_153","type":"agent_message","text":"{\"overall_status\":\"needs_changes\",\"summary\":\"Found 4 new issues in PartnerTables: false empty-state rendering on load failures, table edits cannot clear an area assignment, shared code-settings updates can partially apply and leave data inconsistent, and desktop reordering is still inaccessible to keyboard users.\",\"findings\":[{\"priority\":\"P1\",\"title\":\"Editing a table cannot remove its current area assignment\",\"file\":\"pages/partnertables/versions/partnertables_v1.6_RELEASE.js\",\"line\":1878,\"description\":\"The edit form maps \\\"No area\\\" to an empty string, but `saveTable()` only adds `payload.area` when `tableForm.area` is truthy. Updating an existing table from an area to \\\"No area\\\" therefore sends no `area` field at all, so the record keeps its previous area on the backend and in local state.\",\"suggested_fix\":\"When saving an existing table, always send an explicit cleared value for the link, e.g. `area: tableForm.area || null`, and mirror that in the optimistic state update. If create requests should omit the field, branch create/edit behavior separately.\",\"already_in_bugs_md\":false},{\"priority\":\"P1\",\"title\":\"Area/Table fetch failures are silently shown as an empty page\",\"file\":\"pages/partnertables/versions/partnertables_v1.6_RELEASE.js\",\"line\":400,\"description\":\"`listFor()` swallows every non-429 error and returns `[]`. `reload()` then treats the page as successfully loaded, so a transient backend or network failure renders the normal empty-state UI and leaves create/edit actions enabled. Users can be misled into thinking all areas/tables are gone and create duplicates against data that still exists.\",\"suggested_fix\":\"Propagate non-success fetch failures out of `listFor()` and drive `loadError` from them, or track partial-load failures explicitly so the page stays in an error state instead of masquerading as empty data.\",\"already_in_bugs_md\":false},{\"priority\":\"P2\",\"title\":\"Shared code-settings save can leave partner mode and table codes out of sync\",\"file\":\"pages/partnertables/versions/partnertables_v1.6_RELEASE.js\",\"line\":1507,\"description\":\"In shared-code mode, the handler updates the Partner record and local partner state before rewriting table codes in batches. If any later table update fails, the catch only shows a generic toast; the partner may already be switched to shared mode while only some tables have new `code`/`verification_code` values. That creates inconsistent QR and verification behavior until someone repairs it manually.\",\"suggested_fix\":\"Make the save atomic from the UI's perspective: update all tables first and flip partner settings last, or reload/rollback both partner and table state when any batch step fails. A bulk endpoint/transaction is the safest option.\",\"already_in_bugs_md\":false},{\"priority\":\"P2\",\"title\":\"Desktop reordering is not keyboard-accessible\",\"file\":\"pages/partnertables/versions/partnertables_v1.6_RELEASE.js\",\"line\":452,\"description\":\"`GripHandle` is focusable and exposed with button semantics, but it only supports `onDragStart` and has no keyboard interaction. The same handle is used for area reorder and desktop table reorder, while the move up/down buttons are hidden on `sm` and above. Keyboard users on desktop therefore cannot reorder areas or tables, and the announced \\\"button\\\" is a dead end.\",\"suggested_fix\":\"Provide keyboard reorder controls on all breakpoints or add explicit keyboard semantics for the handle, and remove `role=\\\"button\\\"`/`tabIndex` if the handle remains mouse-only.\",\"already_in_bugs_md\":false}],\"missing_tests\":[\"Regression test that editing a table and selecting \\\"No area\\\" clears the persisted area link.\",\"Failure-path test that Area/Table fetch errors surface `loadError` instead of rendering the empty-state UI.\",\"Failure-path test for shared code-settings save where one table update fails mid-batch and the UI reloads or rolls back to a consistent state.\",\"Accessibility coverage for keyboard-only reordering of areas/tables on desktop.\"],\"notes\":[\"The task referenced `pages/PartnerTables/base/partnertables.jsx`, but the workspace snapshot only exposed the latest implementation through the PartnerTables release artifact reviewed above.\",\"No automated tests were run; this review is based on static inspection of the page snapshot plus `BUGS.md`/`README.md`.\"]}"}}
